;
; Now we're running with the big dogs! Or is that FROM the big dogs?
;
MNUMBER 61
NAME hound
ADJECTIVE 56
PART 0
PART 1
PART 2
PART 9
PART 10
PART 11
PART 12
PART 17
PART 18
PART 19
*DESCRIPTION_START
At a distance, the heart hound could be mistaken for an enormous misshapen
wolf, with its brindled black-gray fur and long tail. But a second glance
reveals its weirdly oversized head. Muscles bulge along the line of its
massive jaw, full of razor-sharp fangs too large for the beast to close its
mouth properly. Lambent green eyes shine with an eerie light that pulses
in time with the rhythm of the heartbeat of its prey.
*DESCRIPTION_END
